fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.http

Interface IHttpEndPoint

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IHttpService, IPlatformConnector

    public interface IHttpEndPoint
    Provides base location information for incoming HTTP connections and upstream HTTP connections.
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

    • Method Detail

      • getProtocol

        String getProtocol()
        Protocol for the end point. For incoming requests, this information may be different to what the end user provides, if for example requests are forwarded by a reverse proxy.
        Returns:
        either HTTP or HTTPS.
        Since:
        1.0

      • getHostName

        String getHostName()
        Hostname for the end point. For incoming requests, this information may be different to what the end user provides, if for example requests are forwarded by a reverse proxy.
        Returns:
        the DNS hostname or the string representation of an IPv4 or IPv6 address, never null.
        Since:
        1.0

      • getHostPort

        int getHostPort()
        TCP port for the end point. For incoming requests, this information may be different to what the end user provides, if for example requests are forwarded by a reverse proxy.

        Defaults are defined for HTTP (80) and HTTPS (443).

        Returns:
        the TCP port number, such as 80 or 443.
        Since:
        1.0

      • getBasePath

        String getBasePath()
        Base path for the end point. For incoming requests, this information may be different to what the end user provides, if for example requests are forwarded by a reverse proxy.
        Returns:
        a string starting with "/" and ending with "/", never null. For end points installed at the server root, this will be "/", for virtual directories and servlet contexts (for example), this typically followings the pattern "/appname/".
        Since:
        1.0
